      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a very common and well-founded critique of trade protectionism. If the price increase for consumers is widespread and significant, the overall economic drag can indeed outweigh the benefits to the sheltered industries. Proponents counter that the long-term benefits—such as technological advancement spurred by domestic production or national security—are more valuable than the short-term price hikes. Ultimately, the \"smartness\" of a tariff hinges on whether the targeted industry can become competitive enough to offset the cost burden placed on the wider economy.",
